deck: A 1974 co-production between Hammer and a Hong Kong Studio. Set in 1904 China. A group of seven ancient vampires of China has lost a member and has fallen to decline. Dracula takes over a Chinese body and sets himself as their new member... and leader.
description: Dracula is opposed by Joseph Van Helsing who was studying the Legend of the seven Golden Vampires. The Chinese vampires and Van Helsing's vampire hunters are depicted as martial artists, following the kung-fu fad of the time. But the two leads' fighting skills are underwhelming.
name: Legend of the 7 Golden Vampires

deck: The first ever Transformers film, it takes place between seasons 2 and 3 of the original TV series.
description: In the year 2005 the war between the heroic Autobots led by Optimus Prime and the evil Decepticons led by Megatron rages on. As both factions fight on a huge evil rises from the depths of space. As the Decepticons launch an all out attack on the Autobot forces the leaders of both factions are mortally wounded, and Prime dies and Megatron is tossed out into space with the other injured Decepticons. After Unicron transforms Megatron into Galvatron and the other Decepticons into his heralds they are sent to retrieve the only thing that can kill Unicron The Matrix of Leadership. The Autobots now under the command of Ultra Magnus and later Hot Rod, must get the Matrix back in order to put a stop to Unicron.
name: Transformers: The Movie

description: The G.I.Joe team fights a bizarre new enemy that threatens to mutate the world's population.  Toss out what you know about Cobra, in this movie we are introduced to Cobra-La, an ancient race that gave birth to Cobra Commander who was to lead a great army and over through man kind.  Not to be outdone the G.I.Joe team also introduces six new characters to help them battle against Cobra-La and its ruler Golobulus.  Wherever there's trouble G.I.Joe is there.
name: G.I. Joe: The Movie

deck:
The second Asterix movie.
Orig. title: Astérix & Obélix: Mission Cléopâtre
name: Asterix & Obelix: Mission Cleopatra

description: He-Man must travel to another dimension, where all he knows will be turned upside-down!
name: The Secret of the Sword

deck:
The first Asterix movie.
Orig. title: Astérix et Obélix contre César
name: Asterix and Obelix vs. Caesar

deck:
The third Asterix movie.
Orig. title; Astérix aux Jeux Olympiques
name: Asterix at the Olympic Games

description: Adapted from the famous comics, this movie follows Tha Fantastic four who were ordinary people until their lives were changed by Cosmic Rays. Reed Richards becomes Mr.Fantastic who is able to stretch any part of his body, and Sue Storm becomes the Invisible Woman who can turn invisible and project force fields, her brother Johnny who becomes the Human Torch has the ability to control and manipulate fire and finally Ben Grimm is turned into the Thing and has super strength. Together the Fantastic four fight evil and try to foil the plans of Doctor Doom.
name: Fantastic Four

deck: The first X-Files movie
name: The X-Files: Fight the Future

deck: Mulder and Scully reunite to solve a series of missing persons cases involving woman and a possible serial killer, but stumble upon something far more bizzarre.
name: The X-Files: I Want to Believe

deck: An 1962 horror comedy with softcore pornography elements. Old Granny Good (Bob Cresse) runs a fairly isolated girls' school in a mountain location. But the school has more than one dark secret.
description:
The initial plot has has young agent Prudence Bumgartner (Laura Eden) enroling at the girls' school to investigate it for illegal activities. Soon established is that the students perform most activities either nude or nearly so. Most of their classes seem to involve physical exercise like jogging or jumping rope. But the school is actualy a front for Granny's moonshine distillery and the center of her smuggling operations.

Much of the actual work in the distillery and the distribution of the moonshine is performed by Granny's assistant, Krackow (William Engesser). Krackow happens to be a werewolf. A school party is also attended by Dracula and the Frankenstein's monster who spike the punch. The drunk girls perform nude dancing before Prudence decides to call the authorities.

Representatives of various agencies soon arrive, including one from the "Society of Protection for Werewolves" . Before Granny is taken away, she offers them all some wine. They fall down drunk and wake up to find themselves in forced labor at the distillery. Prudence naturally among the captives in a not-so-happy ending.
name: House on Bare Mountain

deck: An 1964 horror comedy from the Philippines.
name: Secrets of Dracula

deck: A 1951 live-action film. Clark Kent and Lois Lane cover the opening of the world's deepest oil well in the town of Silsby. The drilling uncovers a small race of Mole Men. Superman has to protect them them from a mob of people wanting to kill the "monsters."
name: Superman and the Mole Men

deck: An 2009 short film, intended as a companion piece to the "Watchmen". Hollis Mason has just published his autobiography. He and various associates are interviewed in a 1970s news show.
name: Under the Hood

deck: A 2006 short film, intended as the pilot to an aborted television series. Atlantis is conquered by invaders. Princess Atlanna barely escapes with her life and that of her son Orin.
description:
The film opens a few years after the escape. Atlanna and her son drive a plane over the Bermuda Triangle when suddenly-appearing cyclones bring it down. Atlanna is abducted by Siren. Orin is left behind with the necklace of his mother and confused memories. A decade later, Orin goes by "Arthur Curry" and barely remembers his mother. He likes diving undersea and feels dolphins are calling to him. In rapid order Arthur discovers his ability to breath underwater, his Atlantean heritage and Siren who came back to finish the job.

The pilot was not broacast in television as originally intended. Instead it was released on the iTunes Store. It became the first show available on iTunes which had not previously aired on a network and soon became a hit.In 2007 it was both released on DVD and received its first television broadcast at YTV, a Canadian television network.
name: Aquaman

deck: This is a live action re-envison of the OVA that was produced by Production I.G in 2000, and the subsequent Manga; Blood: The Last Vampire 2002.
name: Blood: The Last Vampire

deck: Gen13 the animated movie
description:
The film was created in 1998-1999 and was to be released by Buena Vista Pictures, Disney's distributing branch. But then Wildstorm, the company owning the licenced characters, was bought by DC Comics. DC's parent company being Time Warner, an argument about who owned the rights ended with the film shelved.

Disney decided to shelve the film rather than promote a property that had been acquired by a rival studio. It was never released in America and only saw a limited video release overseas.

In 2000, the film received limited video-market release in Europe and Australia. The original version is 73' in length, the uncut one c. 90'.
name: Gen13

deck: A silent motion picture released in 1920 starring Douglas Fairbanks and Noah Beery. It was the first movie version of Zorro.
description: Zorro, masked champion of the people, who appears out of nowhere with flashing sword and an athletic sense of humor fights against the colonial goverment in old Spanish California. The hero is scarring the faces of his enemies and saving the damsel in distress.
name: The Mark of Zorro

deck: This is the 1925 sequel to the 1920 silent film "The Mark of Zorro". Douglas Fairbanks both produced the film and starred as its lead character.
description: Don Diego Vega (Zorro)'s son, Cesar is in Spain finishing his education. Cesar and Don Sebastian of the Queen's Guard compete for the heart of  the beautiful Dolores. But a quarrel ending in violence gives Don Sebastian the chance to dispose of his rival...by framing him for murder!  As a whip-wielding outlaw, Cesar sets out to clear the name of Vega.
name: Don Q, Son of Zorro

deck: "The Beauty... The Beast... The Beat."
description:
In in the dystopian, post-apocalyptic future city of Nuke York, Rock & Rule is an unrated, animated film from Canada. In fact, it is The first animated Canadian film to be shot entirely in Canada.

In the hstory, umanity is dead, supplanted by mutated cats, dogs, and rats. The malevolent megastar, Mok, needs the voice of Angel, member of a punk band, in order to activate a device that will summon a demon from another dimension (voiced by Iggy Pop). All that stands in Mok's way is Omar and the other members of the band.

Featuring music by Iggy Pop, Blondie, Cheap Trick, Lou Reed, and Earth Wind & Fire.

In spite of being considered a box office flop, Rock & Rule has attained some minor cult status, and the movie was adapted for comics in Marvel Comics Super Special #25.
name: Rock & Rule

description: A 1981 film, adapting the legend of Perseus.
name: Clash of the Titans

deck: The motion picture of 1954 is starred James Mason, Robert Wagner, Janet Leigh and Sterling Hayden and was also adapted into a comic book.
description: Young Prince Valiant, son of the exiled King of Scandia, seeks to join the Knights of the Round Table in order to restore his father to his own kingship. He travels to Camelot and and on his journey he uncovers a plot against King Arthur and is tutored by Sir Gawaine, a friend of his father. To prevent the coup d'etat against Arthur, he must uncover the true identity of the Black Knight.
name: Prince Valiant

deck: Doc Savage: The Man of Bronze is a 1975 action film by sci-fi producer George Pál, starring Ron Ely as pulp hero Doc Savage.
description: Doc Savage and his Fabulous Five investigate the death of Doc's father in the wilds of South America. The maniacal and evil Captain Seas tries to thwart them at every turn as they travel to the country of Hidalgo for their investigations.
name: Doc Savage: The Man of Bronze

deck: Final chapter of Rob Zombie's Halloween remakes.
description: Halloween 2, picks up a year after the original Myers incident, Sherrif Brackett (played by Brad Douriff) and his daughter Annie, have taken Lorie Strode into their home. Lorie is visiting a therapist, and things seem to be going well, at least until Dr.Loomis (played by Malcolm Mcdowell) releases a new book revealing that Michael and Lorie are brother and sister. And just as Lorie's world is beginning to crumble Michael comes home.
name: Halloween 2 (2009)

deck: The Modern Day Gentalman Robin Hood is at it again.
name: The Saint's Double Trouble

deck: Battle Royale II: Requiem is a 2003 Japanese, dystopian, action-thriller and a sequel to the film Battle Royale, which was based upon the novel by Koushun Takami. The second film also ties-in with a new manga series called Battle Royale II: Blitz Royale.
description: Three years after the events in the first movie called Battle Royale, Shuya Nanahara is a well-known terrorist, leading a group of Battle Royale survivors called "Wild Seven", who want to bring down the government. In response, the goverment creates the "Battle Royale 2" program, which sends a class of junior-high students to catch and kill the terrorist, who is hiding out on a deserted island.
name: Battle Royale II: Requiem

deck: This direct-to-video movie is a compilation of two similarly-themed episodes of The Flash TV-Series re-edited into a movie-length feature, featuring Mark Hamill as The Trickster.
description: In this adventure the red speedster Barry Allen has to face James Jesse , who vowed to defeat the Flash as the costumed crook, The Trickster, because he had foiled his murder attempt on a private detective. With his insane genius making him seemingly the only villian who can counter the superhero's incredible speed with mundane materials, The Flash has to fight against the Trickster, his sidekick Prank, and a brainwashing device to save Central City.
name: The Flash II: Revenge of the Trickster

deck: This direct-to-video movie is a compilation of two similarly-themed episodes of The Flash TV-Series re-edited into a movie-length feature, where The Flash teams up with Nightshade. This third Flash VHS tape was only released in the United Kingdom.
description: In this adventure the Flash teams up with Nightshade, a now middle-aged costumed hero who was the protector of Central City in his youth. Together they defeat nightshade's greatest enemy, the technological mastermind, The Ghost and hunt down a Nightshade impostor.
name: The Flash III: Deadly Nightshade

deck: This TV movie pilot, features the origin story of the Flash and how he gained the ability to move at superhuman speed.
description: An lab accident gives Central City Police forensic scientist Barry Allen the awesome ability to move at superhuman speed, and he uses them to bring his brother's murderer to justice. But first, Allen must learn to control his sudden, remarkable powers. The S.T.A.R. Labs Doctor Christina "Tina" McGee helps him with this.
name: The Flash

deck: The Mobile Infantry attacks the bugs on their homeworld in this CG animated movie which compiles several episodes of the series into a single animated  movie.
name: Roughnecks: Starship Troopers Chronicles: The Klendathu Campaign

deck: Peter Parker has been framed by the Kingpin, and Daredevil wants to clear his name, but a misunderstanding leads to a confrontation between Daredevil and Spider-Man. They eventually team-up and safe the day!
description:
Episode 1

 

Peter Parker has been framed.His lawyer is the famous Matt Murdick AKA Daredevil. As he is being transported to prison, the police van is blown up and Peter is kidnapped by Richard Fisk. Richard traps Peter leaving him to suffocate in a chamber. As he is about to pass out he is saved by the Man without Fear Daredevil. Daredevil leaves Peter in Matt Murdocks apartment. Matt later talks telling him Daredevil will take care of everything. When Matt leaves, Peter makes a quick change into the Amazing Spider-man. In a flashback scene we see how Peter got a job in Fisk Corparations. It shows how he looked over the projects and change disces. He has to take a disc home and when on his way home he is stopped by the police and FBI as they belive it is the disc that is going to some terroists. In the present day, Spider-man is in Fisk Corpartions seeing how he was set-up. Daredevil is also there and now thinks Spider-man is against Peter. Daredevil attacks Spider-man but Spidey tries telling him he is not against Peter. At that moment Kingpin's  thugs blow the building up and now Daredevil and Spider-man have to escape.
name: Daredevil VS Spider-Man

deck: Based on the comic by Greg Rucka and Steve Lieber.  US Marshall, Carrie Stetko (Beckinsale) has to track down a serial killer in the Arctic.  She meets up with a UN operative (Macht).
name: Whiteout

deck: "A hero born of loss, will clear the path to justice."
name: Masked Rider: The First

deck: President Lex Luthor uses an oncoming Kryptonite meteor to declare Superman and his partner in crime, Batman as public enemies. He places a $1 billion dollar bounty on their heads. Soon it's heroes and villains going after the World's Finest.
description: Superman/Batman: Public Enemiesis a 2009 original direct to video animated superhero film adaptation of "Public Enemies", the opening story arc of DC Comics' Superman/Batman. The story was written by Jeph Loeb and Penciled by Ed McGuinness which focuses on Superman and Batman teaming up to prevent a meteorite from striking Earth and take down Lex Luthor, who has been elected President of the USA. The film is the sixth in the line of the DC Universe Animated Original Movies line released by Warner Premier and Warner Bros. Animation. Voice actors from the DCAU reprised their roles, although it is not a DCAU production and is said not to be connected with that universe beyond sharing of voice actors.
name: Superman/Batman: Public Enemies

deck: Astro Boy is about a young robot with incredible powers created by a brilliant scientist in the image of the son he has lost.
description: Set in futuristic Metro City, Astro Boy is about a young robot with incredible powers created by a brilliant scientist in the image of the son he has lost. Unable to fulfill the grieving man's expectations, our hero embarks on a journey in search of acceptance, experiencing betrayal and a netherworld of robot gladiators, before he returns to save Metro City and reconcile with the father who had rejected him.
name: Astro Boy

deck: Nerdy, reserved bookworm Needy and arrogant, conceited cheerleader Jennifer are best friends, though they share little in common. They share even less in common when Jennifer mysteriously gains an appetite for human blood after a disastrous fire at a local bar. As Needy's male classmates are steadily killed off in gruesome attacks, the young girl must uncover the truth behind her friend's transformation and find a way to stop the bloodthirsty rampage before it reaches her own boyfriend Chip.
name: Jennifer's Body

deck: Li'l Abner becomes convinced that he is going to die within twenty-four hours, so agrees to marry two different girls: Daisy Mae (who has chased him for years) and Wendy Wilecat (who rescued him from an angry mob). It is all settled at the Sadie Hawkins Day race.
description: Set in the mythical town of Dogpatch. Dogpatch has a serious unemployment problem. Men spend their days idling away fishing, and the single women spend time scheming about how to catch their preferred single men come the next Sadie Hawkins Day. Daisy Mae has her sights set on Li'l Abner, but rival, Appasianata, has other plans.
name: Li'l Abner

deck: Li'l Abner is a 1959 musical film based on the comic strip of the same name created by Al Capp.
description: A comedy musical based on an earlier stage musical, which was in turn based on the comic strip characters created by Al Capp. When residents of Dogpatch, USA are notified by the government that they must evacuate, they try to persuade the government that their town is worth saving. Meanwhile, Earthquake McGoon wants to marry Daisy Mae; Daisy Mae wants to marry Li'l Abner, and Li'l Abner just wants to go fishing, until it is learned that Abner's Mammy's Yokumberry Tonic might be enough to save the town. Abner offers the tonic to Washington, but General Bullmoose wants it too, so Bullmoose tries to trap Abner into marrying his attractive but ditzy executive secretary, Appassionata. Meanwhile, Daisy Mae pledges herself to Earthquake in marriage in exchange for rescuing Abner from Bullmoose. Will Abner and Daisy Mae ever finally get together?
name: Li'l Abner

deck: A mediocre voodoo-themed horror film.
description: Dr. Alice Dodgson gets her medical license revoked after the death of one patient. She's facing the possibility of not get any job when she accepts to be the nurse for one young man who suffers of cephallitis called Wesley Claybourne. Aside from the sickness he's suffering Wesley believes he has been "touched" by some voodoo cult. While she stays in Jamaica, Dr. Dodgson will feel uncomfortable as she discovers that voodoo is not only a "state of mind" and could be a real threat to her life and Wesley's. She'll have to discover why she and her patient are targets of the voodoo curse.
name: Tales from the Crypt Presents: Ritual

deck: Six teenagers have discovered the power to fight the forces of evil. Now the fate of the universe is in their hands.
description: Six teenagers Tommy, Kimberly, Adam, Billy, Rocky and Aisha have discovered the power to fight the forces of evil. A giant egg is unearthed in Angel Grove. Lord Zedd and Rita Repulsa investigate the egg, and release the creature inside - Ivan Ooze, whom Zordon had trapped him inside the egg six thousand years ago. Once released, Ooze left to seek revenge on Zordon. And now Zordon in his crystalline deathbed is dying because he has no power, without the power then Zordon of Eltar will never existed. Now the fate of the universe is in their hands. But this time the Power Rangers head for a distant planet to meet up with a bikini-clad warrior babe named Dulcea who imparts ancient wisdom and power. But now that they have their powers back and becomes Power Rangers once more they will now get back to business and defeat Ivan Ooze at all costs.
name: Mighty Morphing Power Rangers The Movie

deck: A new Masked Rider has surfaced, and he appears to be an enemy to the first.
name: Masked Rider: The Next

deck: The long awaited El Superbeasto film was finally unleashed theatrically on Sept. 12, 2009. The home video was made available on the 22nd.
name: The Haunted World of El Superbeasto

deck: The legendary Power Rangers must stop the evil space pirate Divatox from releasing the powerful Maligore from his volcanic imprisonment on the island of Muranthias, where only the kindly wizard Lerigot has the key to release him. The hope of victory lies in the Ranger's incredible new Turbo powers and powerful Turbo Zords.
description: Unlike Mighty Morphin Power Rangers: The Movie, this one is considered canon, taking place within the continuity of the television series. The first episode of Power Rangers: Turbo takes place after the movie. Additionally, unlike the first movie, the appearance was closer to the television show. The Ranger suits were spandex rather than the armor-like suits of the first movie, and the Zords and Megazord were also costumes rather than computer-generated animation. Certain sets and costumes from the movie, such as the Power Chamber set, the Alpha costume, and the Maligore costume were also used in the television show (with the latter being modified and reused as Dark Specter in Power Rangers in Space).
name: Turbo: A Power Rangers Movie

deck: Lara Croft is a wealthy, British archeologist who tries to thwart a secret society seeking two pieces of a mysterious device hidden in two different places of the world in order to use it during a rare planetary alignment to bring them unlimited power to control or destroy the world.
name: Lara Croft: Tomb Raider

deck: Lara Croft is on a quest to save Pandora's box.
name: Lara Croft: Tomb Raider: The Cradle of Life

deck: Some survivors of a drowning ship are rescued by Captain Nemo and his submarine crew. They are taken to an underwater city, where they may be trapped for the rest of their lives.
name: Captain Nemo and the Underwater City

deck: During the US Civil War, Union POWs escape in a balloon and end up stranded on a South Pacific island, inhabited by giant plants and animals. They must use their ingenuity to survive the dangers, and to devise a way to return home.
name: Mysterious Island

deck: Mysterious Island (also called Jules Verne's Mysterious Island) is a 2005 TV film made for Hallmark Channel that is based on Jules Verne's novel of the same name (L'Île mystérieuse).
description: During the Civil War five survivors escape from a prison camp in Richmond, Virginia by hot air balloon and find themselves on an uncharted island in the Pacific. Far from any kind of known civilization, the island is inhabited with carnivorous monsters, bloodthirsty pirates, and mad genius Captain Nemo (Patrick Stewart), who lives on the island for his own secretive ends.
name: Mysterious Island

deck: Casper tells the story of how he became such a good-natured ghost.
name: Casper: A Spirited Beginning

deck: Casper, a ghost, teams up with Wendy, a witch, against an evil warlock.
name: Casper Meets Wendy

deck: Cult classic about a truck driver who battles the spirit of an ancient sorcerer in San Francisco's Chinatown.
name: Big Trouble in Little China

deck: Le Avventure di Topo Gigio is an Italian animated family film. It was the first feature film of Topo Gigio.
name: The Magic World of Topo Gigio

deck: An immortal swordsman by the name of Colin Macleod treks upon the path of vengeance to defeat a ruthless monarch in order to avenge the death of his wife 2000 years ago.
name: Highlander: The Search for Vengeance

deck: Original Masked Rider movie
name: Kamen Rider ZO

deck: When his son is accidentally killed by wreckless teenagers, a grief stricken father asks a witch to summon the vengeance demon Pumpkinhead.
name: Pumpkinhead

deck: A demon who has been imprisoned for centuries is unleashed upon Ireland
name: Rawhead Rex

deck: Animated movie based on the work of the great comic artist from Argentina, Roberto Fontanarrosa.
description: The story revolves around Boogie "el aceitoso" (roughly translated as "the oily"), the best hit man in the city, or at least he thinks so. When the biggest mafia boss in town hires Blackburn (another professional killer, who is starting to take jobs away from Boogie) to get rid of a key witness, Boogie finds out he decides to prove to everyone that he is still number one.
name: Boogie el Aceitoso

deck: Motion comic adding voice acting and some light animation to pre-existing comic book artwork
name: Voltron Revelations: Motion Comic

deck: When it's decided that Hulk is too dangerous for the planet, Earth's mightiest heroes exile him to outer space.
description: When Reed Richards, Tony Stark and Dr. Strange decide the Hulk is too dangerous for earth, Our mightiest heroes exile him to the Planet Sakaar, where The Hulk is forced to be a gladiator.
name: Planet Hulk

deck: Spider-Man is mistaken for a creature of the night by the vampire hunter, Blade.
description: This film actually consists of 1996 episodes of the Spider-Man animated series.
name: Spider-Man Blade the Vampire Hunter

deck: The movie with the adventures of Jiggs and Maggie.
name: Bringing Up Father

deck: Based on "The Surrogates" 5-issue limited series, published by Top Shelf Productions in 2005.
description: In a near future, people live in a seemingly perfect world due to surrogate androids which pretty much substituted them in social interactions overall. However, FBI agent Tom Greer (Bruce Willis) must deal with a conspiracy he discovered envolving those robotic surrogates in the hard way - risking his own life by abandoning his own surrogate and unraveling the mystery by himself.
name: Surrogates

deck: The story of pilot Michel Vaillant, from the French comic.
name: Michel Vaillant

description: A comic strip vamp seeks to seduce her cartoonist creator in order to cross over into the real world.
name: Cool World

deck: Shot in 8 just days, this is the last of the Maggie & Jiggs films as actor Joe Yule died shortly after it was done
name: Jiggs & Maggie Out West

deck: The movie based on movie the World Health Organisation (WHO) doctor and martial arts expert Docteur Justice.
name: Docteur Justice

deck: The last of the Incredible Hulk Television movies as there was to be another movie but, unfortunately, Bill Bixby's health had declined. This Movie is the last in which David Banner hopefully finds a cure to control the raging spirit that dwells within.
name: The Death of The Incredible Hulk

deck: Maggie sues over her resemblance to a cartoon character.
name: Jiggs and Maggie in Court

deck: Also known a Lovely Complex
name: Love * Com The Movie

deck: Female space officer Birdy accidentally almost kills a male high school student while she is pursuing an alien, and is forced to time share her body with the boy while she hunts down criminals from the stars on Earth
name: Birdy the Mighty: Double Trouble

deck: Dave Lizewski is an unnoticed high school student and comic book fan with few friends who lives with his father. His life is not difficult and his personal trials not that overwhelming. One day he makes the decision to become a super-hero even though he has no powers or training.
description: A teenage high-school student struggles with his desire to become a super hero. So in need to satisfy his yearning, he decides, who said you need super powers to be a super hero? Which leads to a gruesome battle between good, evil, and revenge.
name: Kick-Ass

deck: Ultraman live action movie
name: Ultraman The Next

deck: Only a mask stands between the Devil Doctor and world conquest. Heroes and villains search for the tomb of Genghis Khan and the artifacts it contains.
name: The Mask of Fu Manchu

deck: The Doctor returns. Fu Manchu seeks the sceptre of Genghis Khan, which will allow him to unite all of Asia under his rule.
description:
Fu Manchu once again faces Smith and Petrie. But this film adds a third hero to the mix: Allan Parker (Robert Kellard), a young American. Apparently to appeal more to the United States audience. He was never reused.

Curiously, this is the last depiction of Fah Lo Suee in film.
name: Drums of Fu Manchu

deck: A remake of The Mask of Fu Manchu
name: The Face of Fu Manchu

deck: The Doctor seeks revenge against the West. The film was the first sound film featuring the Sax Rohmer character.
name: The Mysterious Fu Manchu

deck: Fu Manchu inoculates 10 women with poison so their kisses will kill world leaders, no kidding, that's really the plot.
name: Blood of Fu Manchu

deck: One of the worst films ever made, the doc plots to freeze all the world's oceans.
description: Made in 1969 and first released in West Germany. Not released elsewhere until 1972. This was the last film where Christopher Lee plays Fu Manchu. This one made it to Mystery Science Theater 3000, however not even Joel and the bots can make this anything but painful.
name: The Castle of Fu Manchu

deck: Based on the obscure strip by Siegel & Shuster that appeared in More Fun Comics before their more famous creation Superman made the scene.
name: Radio Patrol

deck: Made in early 1941 it was released in 1942 barely a month after the attack on Pearl Harbor which boosed it's popularity greatly.
name: Don Winslow of the Coast Guard

deck: Staring Marion Davies the girl friend of the real life Citizen Kane.
name: Tillie The Toiler

deck: If one thing could stop Jack from smilin' it's the war.
name: The Adventures of Smilin' Jack

deck: He who holds the sword rules the world (German)
name: Prince Valiant

deck: Sequel to John Carpenter's 1978 horror classic.
name: Halloween II

deck: The fourth movie in the popular Halloween franchise.
name: Halloween 4: The Return of Michael Myers

deck: The fifth Halloween movie.
name: Halloween 5: The Revenge of Michael Myers

deck: After years of hunting down relatives in an unstoppable coup de blood, the truth of what drives Michael Myers to kill his loved ones comes to light. And will a tiny baby be the secret as to stopping the The Shape from killing again?
description: The sixth film.
name: Halloween: The Curse of Michael Myers

deck: The seventh Halloween movie.
name: Halloween H20: 20 Years Later

deck: the 8th Halloween film
name: Halloween: Resurrection

deck: The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles are in their greatest fight ever when they encounter themselves from another universe.
description: When the turtles of the 1987 animated series are accidentally brought to the world of the 2003 series, the old turtles must ally with the new to prevent Ch'rell, the Utrom Shredder, whose evil plan threatens the existence of the very multiverse itself , leading them to the world of, and to join forces with the turtles of the Mirage comics universe.
name: Turtles Forever

deck: The thief with a heart of gold battles a Nazi cult in the Philippines
name: Palos Strikes Again

deck: Despite it being 20 years since the release of Alyas Palos I and there having been two other Palos between the two, here is Alyas Palos II
name: Alyas Palos II

deck: A faulty blood transfusion turns Dracula's wife into a black woman.
name: Old Dracula

deck: The sequel of Final Fantasy VII  takes place 2 years after Sephiroth is defeated. A new disease called Geostigma has spread throughout the world because of Sephiroth dying and becoming part of the lifestream.
name: Final Fantasy VII Advent Children

deck: 16th Century Sword & Sorcery epic. Featuring the hero created by Robert E. Howard...
description:
Once a mercenary of Queen Elizabeth, fighting Spaniards in Africa, Kane meets the Devil's Reaper and discovers he is bound for hell!

Barely escaping, he soon renounces violence to atone for his past sins, seeking out redemption in a life of peace. That is until the followers of priest-turned-sorcerer Malachi kidnap a Puritan girl, Meredith Crowthorn, and brutally slaughter her family before his very own eyes (including butchering her beloved younger brother Edward who Solomon had befriended). Solomon is forced to take up arms and return to his violent ways once more to rescue her!

In doing so, Kane must return to his birthplace, England, and face his older brother Marcus, who (in his youth) he accidentally left disfigured (and for dead).

But Marcus now serves as merciless enforcer to Malachi. Will Solomon jeopardise his own soul by re-embracing his murderous talents for a higher cause?
name: Solomon Kane
